    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "TL;DR: Strala is rebuilding the foundation of the world’s largest industry - insurance.\n\nIn less than a year, we reached multi seven-figure ARR and are growing 50% MOM. We raised two rounds from Tier 1 funds including Peter Thiel’s Founders Fund, led by the partner who was early in OpenAI, Cognition and Scale AI. Our team comes from institutions like Harvard, Berkeley \u0026 Oxford and firms like Optiver, AMD \u0026 Palantir (+ICPC, NeurIPS backgrounds).\n\n\nWhat we are looking for\n\n - Problem Solver - You love solving hard problems (and have a history of doing so).\n\n - High Agency \u0026 Ownership - You take charge and force things into existence - bonus points if you've been a CTO or founding engineer.\n\n - Proven Builder - 2+ years in backend development and Python, with a track record of fast, production-grade code shipping.\n\n - Core System Design - You own and are responsible for our core infrastructure, databases (PostgreSQL, vector DBs), and architecture.\n\n - Cloud Mastery - You know your way around REST, GraphQL, GCP, AWS, Docker.\n\nYour First Month at Strala\n\n - Ship from Day 1 - You deploy to production on your first day and take full responsibility for your code.\n\n - Ownership - You create specs, you figure shit out, you build features.\n\n - Solve Every Problem - Hiring your next teammate, designing core infrastructure, scaling the existing codebase.\n\nValues\n\n - Ambition: We want to win, and we need to be the best\n\n - Performance: Speed, system thinking, efficiency\n\n - Ownership: When we see a problem, we take ownership of it, and we solve it\n\n - Spirit: Clarity, optimism, meritocracy\n\nWe Offer\n\n - Impact - Shape a company, redefine an industry, and make your code impact millions.\n\n - Intensity - Complex problems, ownership, in-person in SF - we are here to solve problems and win.\n\n - Reward - Interesting work, top quartile salary, top quartile equity.\n\n - Team - Everyone on our team considers themselves the most competitive and intense person they have ever met.\n\n - Zero Barriers - We want the best people and will do whatever it takes. That includes full relocation support, covering all meals and paying for any product that makes you more productive.",
